Etymology. Dedicated in tribute to Mario Vargas Llosa, Peruvian writer and Nobel Prize winner in Literature 2011. Mario Vargas Llosa was born in Arequipa , Peru as N.H., and lived in Bolivia (as the current range of
N. vargasllosai
) the first years of his childhood until he returned back to Peru . He studied Laws in the Universidad Nacional Mayor de San Marcos, alma mater of V.P. and N.H.
